  "birth_place": "Kabinetthaus",
  "description": "Prussian philosopher, government official, diplomat, and educator (1767–1835)",
  "bio": "弗裡德利希·威廉·克里斯蒂安·卡爾·費迪南·馮·洪堡（德語：Friedrich Wilhelm Christian Carl Ferdinand von Humboldt，1767年6月22日—1835年4月8日）又譯洪堡特，是一位德國哲學家、語言學家、政府官員和外交家，也是柏林洪堡大學的建立者。\n威廉·馮·洪堡是德國文化史上影響最深刻和最偉大的人物之一。他與弟弟亞歷山大都有廣博的學識，並對當時的時代有著歷史上少見的巨大影響。亞歷山大主要研究的是自然科學，而威廉的研究物件是文化科學，如教育學、國家理論、對語言、文學和文化的分析。他是普魯士教育改革的推動者，同時也是普魯士的外交官。",
  "bio_source": "zhwiki",
  "description_en": "Prussian philosopher, government official, diplomat, and educator (1767–1835)",
  "bio_en": "Friedrich Wilhelm Christian Karl Ferdinand von Humboldt (22 June 1767 – 8 April 1835) was a Prussian philosopher, linguist, government functionary, diplomat, and founder of the Humboldt University of Berlin. In 1949, the university was named after him and his younger brother, Alexander von Humboldt, a naturalist.\nHe was a linguist who made contributions to the philosophy of language, ethnolinguistics, and to the theory and practice of education.",
  "bio_en_source": "enwiki"
}